1.) you type in an address on personal computer
-the request is sent to the server which is the URL

2.) server responds to the request 

Where and how do website come into play?
*front end (this is what the client/user sees)
-Webpages are made from HTML (structuring) and CSS (stylizing)
-Javascript allows for interaction

*back end (this is what the server does)
-the code that is done to the information held
by the front page
-these are generally scripts used to process 
the information
-these include databases
-ex. importing and exporting files

You should have a .css file for all of your html files so that 
you can have an organized and set style